# BROWSER-core.md - Twitter/X Global Rules & Shared Patterns

🚨 `profile: "{{browser_profile}}"` on EVERY browser call.

## Selectors

| Element | Selector |
|---------|----------|
| Tweet article | `article[data-testid="tweet"]` |
| User name | `[data-testid="User-Name"]` |
| Tweet text | `[data-testid="tweetText"]` |
| Tweet link | `a[href*="/status/"]` |
| Reply button | `[data-testid="reply"]` |
| Like button | `[data-testid="like"]` → `[data-testid="unlike"]` when liked |
| Retweet button | `[data-testid="retweet"]` |
| Views | `a[href*="/analytics"] span` |
| Textarea (reply) | `[data-testid="tweetTextarea_0"]` |
| Textarea (dialog) | `[role="dialog"] [data-testid="tweetTextarea_0"]` |
| Submit button (reply) | `[data-testid="tweetButtonInline"]` |
| Submit button (dialog) | `[role="dialog"] [data-testid="tweetButton"]` |
| Follow button | `[data-testid$="-follow"]` (text "Follow"/"Follow Back") |
| Compose | `a[href="/compose/tweet"]` or `[data-testid="SideNav_NewTweet_Button"]` |

## § 1 — Typing (CDP approach)

🚨 NEVER use execCommand('insertText') as the FIRST input — button stays disabled. Draft.js needs CDP `type` to initialize the editor state. After CDP `type` initializes it, `execCommand` works for appending subsequent lines.
🚨 NEVER use textContent/innerHTML/value — causes malformed/duplicated text.

**CDP type with NARROW selectors (primary method):**

🚨 **NEVER include `\n` in type text** — the CLI passes it as literal characters (backslash + n), not newlines.

**For replies (on tweet page) — single paragraph, no formatting:**
```
1. snapshot('[data-testid="tweetTextarea_0"]') → textbox [ref=eNN]
2. browser.type(ref, "single paragraph text with no newlines")
3. snapshot('[data-testid="tweetButtonInline"]') → Reply button [ref=eNN]
4. browser.click(buttonRef)
```

**For compose dialog (original tweet, quote tweet) — clipboard paste approach:**

🚨 `execCommand("insertText")` creates visual text BUT Draft.js drops it on submit. CDP `type` + Enter keys also loses body lines. **ONLY clipboard paste reliably persists multiline content in Draft.js.**

🚨 **Emojis get stripped** by Draft.js on serialize — even if they show in editor. Use text-based formatting (→, -, •) instead of emoji bullets.

**Full flow (ONE evaluate — clear + paste + submit):**
```javascript
async () => {
  await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000));
  var ta = document.querySelector('[role="dialog"] [data-testid="tweetTextarea_0"]');
  if (!ta) return { error: 'no textarea' };
  ta.focus();
  // Clear any residual text
  document.execCommand('selectAll');
  document.execCommand('delete');
  await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300));
  // Paste full tweet as HTML (line breaks = <br>)
  var text = ${JSON.stringify(tweetText)};
  var dt = new DataTransfer();
  dt.setData('text/html', text.replace(/\n/g, '<br>'));
  dt.setData('text/plain', text);
  ta.dispatchEvent(new ClipboardEvent('paste', { clipboardData: dt, bubbles: true, cancelable: true }));
  await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));
  // Submit
  var btn = document.querySelector('[role="dialog"] [data-testid="tweetButton"]');
  if (!btn || btn.disabled) return { error: 'button disabled', text: ta.innerText.slice(0, 100) };
  btn.click();
  await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
  return { posted: !document.querySelector('[role="dialog"]'), len: text.length };
}
```

**Format rules for original tweets:**
- Hook line first (standalone, punchy)
- Blank line between sections (`\n\n`)
- Body lines: text-based bullets (→, -, •) — NOT emojis (Draft.js strips them on submit)
- @mentions typed as text (auto-linked by Twitter)
- Hashtags on last line (3 max)
- ❌ NEVER use emojis as bullet points — Draft.js strips them on serialize
- ❌ NEVER use `execCommand("insertText")` for body lines — Draft.js drops them on submit
- ❌ NEVER use bold — fragile with Draft.js

🚨 Home page has a feed textarea AND a dialog textarea. Using `[data-testid="tweetTextarea_0"]` alone → `strict mode violation` (2 elements). ALWAYS scope to dialog.
🚨 If click returns "Element not found" (stale ref from dialog animation), use evaluate fallback:
```javascript
evaluate(() => { document.querySelector('[role="dialog"] [data-testid="tweetButton"]').click(); return { clicked: true }; })
```

🚨 **NEVER use full-page snapshot** (no selector) — returns 7-10KB. The narrow selectors above return ~31b each (99.7% reduction).

## § 5 — Like + Read + Dedup (combined — ONE evaluate on post page)

After navigating to a tweet page, this single evaluate likes the tweet, reads its full text, detects media, and checks if we already replied. Saves 1 step per tweet vs separate like + read.

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    var articles = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('article[data-testid="tweet"]'));
    var target = articles[0];
    if (!target) return { error: 'no article' };
    var text = (target.querySelector('[data-testid="tweetText"]') || {}).innerText || '';
    var hasMedia = !!target.querySelector('[data-testid="tweetPhoto"]') || !!target.querySelector('[data-testid="videoPlayer"]');
    var likeBtn = target.querySelector('[data-testid="like"]');
    if (likeBtn) likeBtn.click();
    var alreadyLiked = !!target.querySelector('[data-testid="unlike"]');
    var alreadyReplied = articles.some(function(a) {
      var user = a.querySelector('[data-testid="User-Name"]');
      return user && user.innerText.includes('@{{handle}}');
    });
    return { text: text.slice(0, 300), hasMedia: hasMedia, liked: !!likeBtn, alreadyLiked: alreadyLiked, alreadyReplied: alreadyReplied };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

- `alreadyReplied: true` → track + skip
- `hasMedia && text.length < 80` → likely meme/image post, skip (can't see image)
- `alreadyLiked: true` → already liked, no action needed

To like a specific tweet on a feed/search page (without the combined read):
```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    const tweets = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('article[data-testid="tweet"]'));
    const target = tweets.find(t => {
      const link = t.querySelector('a[href*="/status/"]');
      return link?.getAttribute('href')?.includes('/${tweetId}');
    });
    if (!target) return { error: 'tweet not found' };
    const likeBtn = target.querySelector('[data-testid="like"]');
    if (!likeBtn) {
      if (target.querySelector('[data-testid="unlike"]')) return { already_liked: true };
      return { error: 'like button not found' };
    }
    likeBtn.click();
    return { clicked: true };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```
